rooms.Name: The Entrance to a vast Underground City
rooms.Description:
You are at the entrance to a small mysterious city.  A great adamantite gate
lies to the north, limitting access to the city.

Exits.Description: A huge gate opens to the north allowing passage into the city.

ExtraDescs.Description: A large adamantite gate with giant spider shaped emblems stands here.

rooms.Name: Southern Drow Square
rooms.Description:
You enter a large central square of the drow city.  Travellers of all sorts move
about the courtyard freely. Exits leave in all directions.

Exits.Description: A large adamantium gate lies to the south

rooms.Name: Drow Courtyard
rooms.Description:
The size of this courtyard would amaze even the biggest of all creatures within
the realm.  It seems to be a place that the drow people use for celebrations
and every day life activity.  To the west appears to be an alley or a back
street. A little spider scurries out from under your feet.

rooms.Name: Drow Courtyard
rooms.Description:
This corner of the courtyard appears to be no different then the rest. Small
debris trickles across the ground due to the light breeze.  Exits lead in all
directions.

rooms.Name: Eastern Drow Courtyard
rooms.Description:
This is the eastern most point of the courtyard.  Travellers of all shapes and
sizes share stories with each other as they interact.  For some reason you do
not seem to fit in here.

rooms.Name: Center of Drow Square
rooms.Description:
This is the center of this enourmous courtyard.  Drow common folk move around
doing there normal day-to-day activities.  To the far north you make out the
faint outline of the drow place of worship.  Exits lead in all directions.

rooms.Name: Western Drow Courtyard
rooms.Description:
The size of this courtyard continues to amaze you. This is the western most end
of the courtyard.  Small spiders seem to be moving from east to west everytime
you notice one.

rooms.Name: City street
rooms.Description:
You walk along a highly ornate city street leading east-west.  To the north
lies the guild of the cleric class and to the south that of the mage.

rooms.Name: Entrance to the Mage's Guild
rooms.Description:
The mage - the mage is a hard char to play if you are new to the game.  Most 
find the mage really hard to level and hard to keep alive due to its lack of
hit points.  They are usually best when in large groups needing extra power.
The mage hold some really powerful spells and are capable of being very 
useful if you know how to use them.  Here you stand in the entrance to the
mage guild.

rooms.Name: Spike's Bar
rooms.Description:
Here yo are in the bar of choice for the mage.  Spik'es Bar is a well known
bar bt seems to be losing it's popularity among the patrons of the realm.  It
still serves as a nice place to shoot some stick and grab a couple drinks.

rooms.Name: Guildmaster's Inner Sanctum
rooms.Description:
The sanctum of your guildmaster - Here, one may practice the arts that the mage
class has developed through the centuries.  The guildmaster is very capable
of teaching you all the spells you will need to know during your stay here at
ROI. Your guildmaster sits in the corner waiting to assist you.

rooms.Name: Entrance to the Cleric's Guild
rooms.Description:
The cleric - A relatively easy character to play for a person with patience.
Har to level in the later levels, the cleric is an essential part of any big
group. Good clerics get much respect within the realms.  You stand here in 
the entrance to the guild.

rooms.Name: The Bar
rooms.Description:
Just your typical bar.  Patrons of clerical descent walk around enjoying a 
couple drinks and sharing stories.  A waiter is here to get you your spirits.

rooms.Name: Guildmaster's Inner Sanctum
rooms.Description:
The guildmaster's inner sanctum - Here the guildmaster stands waiting to help
you learn the tricks of the clerical trade.

rooms.Name: City street
rooms.Description: You walk along a highly ornate city street leading north and west.

rooms.Name: City street
rooms.Description: You walk along a highly ornate street running north-south. Not much is going on over here.

rooms.Name: City Street
rooms.Description:
You walk along a highly ornate city street within the drow commons.  The street
continues in a east-west direction, while another exit leads off to the south.

rooms.Name: City street
rooms.Description:
You walk along a highly ornate city street. To the north lies the entrance
to the thieve's guild.

rooms.Name: Entrance to the Thieve's Guild
rooms.Description:
The thief - the thief is one of the easiest characters to play on the realm.
They level faster than most other classes here.  One problem with the thief
is that their usefullness comes randomly and sometimes rarely.  The thieve's
deadly backstab is a very lethal weapon.

rooms.Name: The Brickyard
rooms.Description: An up and coming bar in the drow area. This bar is commonly mentioned when thinking of good beer specials and occassionally when a good band comes to the area. A nice place to just kick back and enjoy some spirits.

rooms.Name: Guildmaster's Inner Sanctum
rooms.Description:
You have entered the guildmaster's inner sanctum.  Daggers stck in the wall
and broken chairs make you wonder if the old man sitting in the shadows can
teach you anything.  Although old in his age, he gleems of knowledge and wisdom.

rooms.Name: Drow Courtyard
rooms.Description:
This north-eastern corner of the courtyard is busy like the rest.  To the east
lies a city street while other exits lead back towards the courtyard.

rooms.Name: Northern-End of Drow Courtyard
rooms.Description:
This the the far northern end of the courtyard.  To the north lies Drow Main
Street and the temple of the Drow city.  Noises can be heard coming from the
north.

rooms.Name: Drow Courtyard
rooms.Description:
This bustling city revolves around the activity of his people. To the north 
lies the General Store while other exits lead off in all directions.

rooms.Name: A Back Alley
rooms.Description:
You have entered a back alley way.  To the north lies the guild of the ranger.
This alley contiunes to the west.

rooms.Name: A Back Alley
rooms.Description:
This alley way continues to the south and back to the east.  Sounds from the
city can be faintly heard from here.  To the south you see a good size spider
crawl up the city wall.

rooms.Name: The Tunnel of Terror
rooms.Description:
You have entered a narrow tunnel which is densly covered with cobwebs.  You 
can see a pair of gleeming red eyes further down the tunnel. A very itchy
feeling crawls over your skin.

Exits.Description: An entrance to a tunnel is here.

rooms.Name: Deeper into the Tunnel
rooms.Description:
This is a very strange tunnel.  Chunks of the wall seem to be carved out as if
though someone or something has been using the wall as a sharpening tool.  The
room seems to be getting even thicker with cobwebs. You feel very uneasy.

rooms.Name: The end of the Tunnel
rooms.Description:
What was that?! A big furry legged spider just crossed across your eyes. A 
number of cacoon shaped objects can be found strung from the ceiling.  A cool
breeze passes through the tunnel which makes you recollect that feeling just 
before you heard your last death announcement.

rooms.Name: Before the Web
rooms.Description:
As you venture deeper into this tunnel, the walls seem to slope slightly 
downward while you fight your way through small cobwebs.  You can feel a great
deal of energy coming from this room.  Something is not right here. You feel as
though your very existance is in danger.

rooms.Name: The Web
rooms.Description:
You have entered into a cavern bare on the northern and southern walls, but 
decorated with a enourmous tapestry like web on the western wall.  The 
beauty of this web is magestic and seems to put you in a trance.  Besides
the pike of assorted bones beneath the web, you would think that this was a
beautiful treasure you just found.

rooms.Name: Entrance to the Ranger's Guild
rooms.Description:
The ranger - A very skilled class with the ability to render its victim 
helpless. A wise choice in adventurer if you are unfamiliar with your 
surroundings. Some find the ranger a little frustrating and hard to handle.

rooms.Name: Alex's Cantina
rooms.Description:
A very poplar bar of the drow people.  Many gather here after a long days work
and drink down a few cold ones. At night, this bar is hoppin with live dance
music and is a great social surrounding.

rooms.Name: Guildmaster's Inner Sanctum
rooms.Description:
The sanctum of your guildmaster - Here one may practice the arts that the  
ranger kind have developed over its relatively short existance.  The room
seems to have a spiritual feeling and you notice your guildmaster sitting in
the corner waiting to help you.

rooms.Name: A Back Alley
rooms.Description:
Litter and debris line this alley way.  From the looks of it, it would appear 
that not many travelers venture into this part of the city - not even the drow
people. Exits lead north and south.  Something about this room pulls your
soul into your stomach.

rooms.Name: A back Alley
rooms.Description:
This alley way continues to the north and back towards the courtyard to the
east. Faint sounds coming from the courtyard can stil be heard.

rooms.Name: A Back Alley
rooms.Description: You have entered into a back alley way. To the east is the drow courtyard while to the west you can't yet determine what your future holds.

rooms.Name: City Street
rooms.Description:
You have come to the end of this city street.  Another street intersects this
one to your east.

rooms.Name: Entrance to the Warrior's Guild
rooms.Description:
The warrior - the warrior is one of the easier classes to control.  Built with
brute strength, the warrior kin are the bulk of most any group.  Although 
adapt in fighting, the warrior kin lacks the ability of magic.  You stand in
the warrior's guild.

rooms.Name: Midnight Way
rooms.Description:
You are on Midnight Way.  By the look of it, you can figure out pretty easily,
why this street is named such.  Dark shadows loom in from what little light
comes into this street.

rooms.Name: Midnight Way
rooms.Description:
It would appear that you have come to the end of the street. to the south is
the local watering hole while the street continues in the direction you came 
from.

rooms.Name: Water Shop of the Lost Traveler
rooms.Description:
The heat and humidity of the realms will bring great thirst to your body.
Here, the shopkeeper can help you control your thirst with his wares. He has
a list of things to sell you.

rooms.Name: Midnight Way
rooms.Description:
Midnight Way, runs north-south along the eastern most part of the city's
boundaries. Silent as a ninja in the dark, this street gives you a very
creepy feeling

rooms.Name: Midnight Way
rooms.Description: Midnight way, so named for the darkness which unnaturally falls on this street, runs north-south from here.

rooms.Name: Midnight Way
rooms.Description:
As light seeps into this street as you continue north, you can make out small
figures cowering in the remaining shadows. The light from the north, faintly
outlines a small shop hidden away in the corner.

rooms.Name: The Unholy Statistician
rooms.Description:
Besides what your guildmasters can teach you, the statistician can give you
powers like no one else can. Sent as a prophet from a higher power, he can make
alterations to your soul with swirl of a finger.

rooms.Name: WidowMaker
rooms.Description:
This particular street has a crooked twist in it. The walls seem to slant in
obscure directions and seem to be made of some unusal type of rock.

rooms.Name: WidowMaker
rooms.Description:
Here the street bends to the north. A small shop lies to your west while 
you continue on your journey throw the drow combines.

rooms.Name: Penny-anti Armory
rooms.Description:
The walls are lined with pieces of equipment that appear to be under repair.
A glowing light comes from beneath the shopkeepers counter.  Maybe he does
have something of worth afterall.

rooms.Name: WidowMaker
rooms.Description: As a small spider scuries from underneath your foot step, it reminds you of how fortunate you are to be so big. Well at least in your mind anyway.  This street appears to only have exits leading north-south

rooms.Name: Intersection of Oliver Lane & WidowMaker
rooms.Description: This intersection is a very busy part of town. Drow commoners leave off west to go worship while other fell-o's stand around conversing.

rooms.Name: WidowMaker
rooms.Description:
You stand at the end of WidowMaker.  You can hear the sounds of the city coming
from the south while the exit to the east appears to lead to a much quieter
part of the city.

rooms.Name: A Dusty Side Street
rooms.Description:
This little side street is covered with dust.  The swirl of dust makes it hard
to see and has a blinding effect. From what you can make out, there appears to
be an exit to the south

rooms.Name: A Dusty Side Street
rooms.Description:
As you continue through the swirl of dust, it only seems to get thicker and
thicker. You should probably get out of here.

rooms.Name: A Dust Storm
rooms.Description:
The swirl of dust FRINGES your skin! OUCH! as small debris kicks up and hits
you in the head you realize that you have made a wrong turn.

rooms.Name: The General Store
rooms.Description:
Little knick knacks line the walls of this shop.  Here, one can buy some of the
necessities that might be needed during the may adventures within the realm.
Make sure you have everything you need and the cash for it.

rooms.Name: The Musty Bakery
rooms.Description:
The smell of fresh baked goods immediately entice your hunger.  The baker here
has a list of fine goods to sell you.  To the east lies the might temple of
Yochlol.

rooms.Name: News of the Forgotten fool
rooms.Description:
This is a small room which is lined with small pieces of furniture.  News of
upcoming events and other things can be found on the board.  Travellers stand
here looking at the board.

rooms.Name: The Black-Magic Shop
rooms.Description:
All types of potions and scrolls line the shelves of this small room.  The s
shopkeeper is here to help you find what you need.

rooms.Name: Wicked Dagger Weapon Shop
rooms.Description:
All types of weapons can be purchased here for various prices.  To see what 
the shop keeper has take a look at the list on the counter.

rooms.Name: Guildmaster of the Unholy
rooms.Description:
As you enter this room, you can feel all the forces of evil creep within your
soul. The guildmaster of the Antipaladin race, stands before you surrounded
by a deadly aura.

rooms.Name: drow production room
rooms.Description:
this room is just for holding more mobs that will come out as the game goes
on.

rooms.Name: Paladin's & AntiPaladin's Guild
rooms.Description:
This is the entrance to the guild of the multi paladins.  Split at creation,
myth has it that the antipaladin is the evil brother of its holy counterpart,
the paladin.  Stairs going up lead to a social gathering of travelers.

rooms.Name: Toe's Tavern
rooms.Description:
Adventurers of the Paladin kin sit here and jovialy put down some spirits and
brab about their travels.  Anotherset of stairs lead up while a dark dismal
room leads off to the west.

rooms.Name: Guildmaster of the Holy
rooms.Description:
Your guildmaster is here to help you learn the tricks of the trade.  By 
PRACTICING, you can advance your knowledge in various attributes.  For some 
ominous reason the noise from the bar below can not be heard from within
the guildmaster's sanctum.  This room feels very sacred.

rooms.Name: The Dark Passage
rooms.Description:
This passage is the entry way to the great arena up above.  Sounds of swords
clanging and chains smashing on the ground fil this room.

rooms.Name: Arena of Death
rooms.Description:
Adventurers of all kin come here to do battle.  Blood is scatterd about and
broken shields, bats swords armor, etc can bee seen all about.

rooms.Name: Arena of Death
rooms.Description:
The blood stained ground here emits a horrible odor. More broken items litter
the battle area here.

rooms.Name: Arena of Death
rooms.Description: This arena was built for one thing as its intentions -- killing!  Body parts of those who have tried there luck strewn the grounds here.

rooms.Name: Arena of Death
rooms.Description:
Similar to every other corner of this battle field, this room is in the same
condition as the rest. Broken bones and equipment lie before you.

rooms.Name: Arena of Death
rooms.Description:
Just another place where killing in mass quantities has taken place.  The 
ground here is saturated with blood.  Exits lead off in all directions.

rooms.Name: Arena of Death
rooms.Description: A less fought in corner of the arena. Maybe this is where you should spill your blood. To the north lies the entrance to the arena.

rooms.Name: The Dark Pitstop
rooms.Description:
This thriving bar is a rest stop for weery travellers. Warrior type adventurers
move about the room toasting each others success.  A waiter is here to help
you.

rooms.Name: Beach Shack
rooms.Description:
Once a thriving nightclub/bar, this place is now a small privately own eatery.
The bar owner has moved on and is now promoting other local clubs.  Nothing
goes on here anymore

rooms.Name: Guildmaster's Inner Sanctum
rooms.Description:
You are in the guildmaster's inner sanctum.  Weapons of all type line the walls
while other warrior type seem to be fine tuning their skills.  Your guildmaster
awaits your bidding.

rooms.Name: Oliver Lane - West
rooms.Description:
The path you were following comes to an abrut stop here.  Looking at the wall
to the west you can see a an inscription which looks like a small tunnel with
a large web at the end.

rooms.Name: Oliver Lane - West
rooms.Description:
You are on a very un populated section of this road.  Sounds of whips can
be heard to your west.

rooms.Name: Oliver Lane - West
rooms.Description: A very quiet street. Not much traffic comes down this direction it would appear.

rooms.Name: Entrance to the Dark Temple
rooms.Description:
The huge temple looms over you from here.  You can make out some faint markings
of a large spider above the door of the temple.  A very quiet street leads to
the west and also branches to the east.

rooms.Name: Oliver Lane - East
rooms.Description:
This part of the street leads towards a very populous area within the drow
city. As common folk cruise by, you wonder if there is something going on
that you do not know about.

rooms.Name: Oliver Lane - East
rooms.Description:
The sounds of a thriving community can distinctly be heard from here.  A major
intersection lies to the east, while the exit to the west runs back towards
the temple.

rooms.Name: Drow Main Street
rooms.Description:
This is a very busy section in the drow city.  To the east lies the Post Office
fo writing other adventurers.  The west exit leads towards the arena where
travelers can sharpen their skills, while the ominous temple can be seen to 
the north.

rooms.Name: Drow Main Street
rooms.Description:
This section of the street looks nothing different from the rest. Exits lead
off to the north and south.

rooms.Name: Drow Main Street
rooms.Description:
This street is scattered with debris and small spiders.  The sounds of the 
courtyard can be heard to the south while people seem to be moving to the 
north.

rooms.Name: The Lobby to the Post Office
rooms.Description:
This is the lobby to the Post Office.  To the east lies the post master.  This
room is extravagantly decorated with rugs and tapestries.  Small chairs line
the northern wall.

rooms.Name: The Post Office
rooms.Description:
This is the post office.  From here you can send and receive mail.  the 
postmaster is very reliable in the handling of your mail. What mal goes through
him is confidential.

rooms.Name: Foyer of the Dark Temple
rooms.Description:
Upon entering this large temple you feel a cold chill pass through the room.
There are satanic markings around every corner.  By the appearnace of this 
massive temple you can only imagine the size of the rest of the city.  This
temple is obviously what the drow civilization operates around.

rooms.Name: South-Eastern Corner of the Dark Temple
rooms.Description:
A huge statue of the almighty yochlol stands in the center of this room. Looking
at this specimen reminds you of how good it is to be human. You hope you never
meet this hideous creature face to face.

rooms.Name: North-Eastern Corner of the Dark Temple
rooms.Description:
This end of the temple is very similar to the rest.  To the east lies the magic
shop. The evilness of this room sends a chill down your spine

rooms.Name: Northern-end of the Dark Temple
rooms.Description:
You are in the northern end of the temple.  More sadistic markings can be
found here along with a huge mural on the floor that seems to stretch into
other rooms in all directions. To the north is the gild of the paladin kind.

rooms.Name: North-western corner of the Temple
rooms.Description:
This corner is no different from the other rooms of the temple.  More strange
markings an scattered debris can be found in this room.

rooms.Name: South-Western Corner of the Dark Temple
rooms.Description:
Portraits of the great arachnid yochlol line this ocrner of the temple.  To the
west lies the reading room whereas to the east, the entrance/exit to the temple.
